4. Output:

Probability of Event: 0.82 (Likely)

ğŸ“Œ Notes & Limitations
	â€¢	Logistic regression assumes a linear relationship between features and the log-odds of the event.
	â€¢	Requires clean and relevant data for reliable predictions.
	â€¢	Not suitable for complex, highly non-linear problems (consider other models if performance is poor).
	â€¢	Outputs are probabilities, not certainties â€” they should guide, not dictate, decisions.
